{
  "text": "ANN is a system with the ability to predict a set of input variables into a set of outcomes [CITATION_1] , which has been successfully applied to investigate the possible interactions of reaction parameters and to optimize various valuable ester synthesis by lipase [CITATION_2] . The present study used ANN for performing the experimental design of 2-ethylhexyl salicylate synthesis in a solvent-free system. The independent parameters selected for the experimental design, namely, reaction temperature, reaction time, and enzyme amount, and their ranges, as well as levels, are listed in Table 1 . In this study, the data generated from BBD design (Table 1) ",
